"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also noted that, despite having covered several sports events in the past, the Olympics would present a uniquely different experience.\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He expressed his anticipation and enthusiasm for this exciting assignment.\", \"from\": 413, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Being a photojournalist of repute, Rituraj achieved significant recognition in 2018 when he was awarded India's prestigiousRamnath Goenka Awardin the spot news category.\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9998851670302166, \"rank\": 0.00011480770147772484, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His accomplishments extend beyond this accolade, as he also completed an exclusive three-year training program in photojournalism organized by World Press Photo from 2001 to 2003.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Press_Photo\", \"score\": 0.9999978063930443, \"rank\": 2.193611738649834e-06, \"text\": \"World Press Photo\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Press_Photo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Press_Photo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This specialized training further enhanced his skills and contributed to his esteemed reputation in the field.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Currently serving as theSenior Special News Photographer for The Hindu, he has built a distinguished career in the field.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the Paris Olympics 2024, Rituraj will be among the select few sports photographers from India chosen to cover the event, reflecting his esteemed position and expertise in the industry.\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9998851670302166, \"rank\": 0.00011480770147772484, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Renowned for his extensive work documenting the socio-political landscape of Northeast India, Ritu Raj has also undertaken special projects focusing on the diverse ethnic groups in the region.\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\", \"score\": 0.9999999174822313, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ritu Raj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A photograph, captured by Ritu Raj Konwar, The Hindu's Guwahati-based Special News Photographer, served as the inspiration for the Malayalam film *Ottal*, which recently won two National Awards.\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1486, \"end\": 1494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ritu Raj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ritu_Raj\"}, {\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7576240762812626e-29, \"text\": \"The Hindu\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\"}, {\"begin\": 1591, \"end\": 1600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malayalam\", \"score\": 0.5981586760121678, \"rank\": 0.671777118216773, \"text\": \"Malayalam\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malayalam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malayalam\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Directed by Jayaraj, the film received accolades for Best Environmental Film and Best Adapted Screenplay.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jayaraj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with The Hindu, Jayaraj explained that the photograph had a profound impact on him, haunting his thoughts and leading him to incorporate a similar scene into his film.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1783, \"end\": 1792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7576240762812626e-29, \"text\": \"The Hindu\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Hindu\"}, {\"begin\": 1794, \"end\": 1801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jayaraj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He shared that the image allowed him to connect with Anton Chekhov's short story \\\"Vanka,\\\" which he had long wished to adapt for the screen.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Chekhov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6425903036133633e-23, \"text\": \"Anton Chekhov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Chekhov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Chekhov\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jayaraj credited Konwar's photograph as a pivotal influence on the creation of *Ottal*.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2087, \"end\": 2094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jayaraj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Konwar had taken the photograph during theAssam floodslast August in Morigaon district.\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2245, \"end\": 2262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morigaon_district\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Morigaon district\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morigaon_district\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morigaon_district\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the film's success, Jayaraj reached out to Konwar, expressing a desire to locate the boy featured in the picture and offer assistance in any possible way.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2294, \"end\": 2301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jayaraj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jayaraj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born and raised in Guwahati and hailing from Mangaldoi on the north bank of the mighty Brahmaputra, Ritu Raj holds a master's degree in anthropology.\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guwahati\",